        Official Singles Chart on 3/2/2023

        3 February 2023 - 9 February 2023

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        the carpenters cont'd...so as you see, the carpenters have an awesome catalog, hard to just pick 10 of their best songs. :)))))

        10. 'it's going to take some time' *#12 on the hot 100, didn't make uk chart. during this time the carpenters were notching top 10-20 hit after another here in the states. their sound, esp. karen's singing, was perfect for u.s. radio-1972* https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=c0UpuD3u0po

        11. 'only yesterday' *#4-hot 100, #7-uk, another of richard's personal faves & perfectly showcases their harmonies off their 'horizon' album that richard produced, great album, 1 of my very faves!* 1975-https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=p8JjKMC4yq4

        12. 'merry xmas darling' 1970-*their signature xmas song over here, over the years billboard had a xmas singles chart, would combine xmas songs on the hot 100, back & forth, etc. so this song tech. never made the hot 100 chart. but @ the end of the song is the 'carpenters sound' that richard wanted and would use in many of their future music. https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=PB5c-KmxqQw

        13. 'superstar' *#2 here, #18 uk, one of richard's very faves and according to richard, karen needed only 1 take!* 1971: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=MhkTyJstQWE

        14. 'strength of a woman'-1981 *not a single, but off their 'made in america' album. both karen's & richard's fave carpenters album of all time, karen sounds amazing on this one!*
        https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=4QcFK-LGJL4

        15. 'hurting each other'-1972 *#2 hot 100 (during their string of constant top 10's on the hot 100), didn't make uk chart, but again :D karen sounds superb on this one!* https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=SQy01w-yyo4

        enjoy everyone! lemme know if you have any questions/requests about the carpenters or other past u.s. acts. ;)

        the carpenters were mostly known for ballads and love songs and older brother richard produced much of their music. so i'll do a carpenters mix *in no particular order* of some of their biggest hits, richard's & karen's personal faves and also mine :D and 1 warning: 1 listen to karen's beautiful silky voice, you could become addicted like me! :D they achieved top 10 *late 60s-early 80s, but very big in the 70s. michael jackson was a huge fan of theirs, the jackson 5 & the carpenters,as well as mj's early solo hits, would be in the hot 100 top 10 together a handful of times* hits all over the world, but esp. in the u.s., england and japan:

        1. 'we've only just begun' *1 of their biggest hits of all time on the billboard hot 100, #2 here #28 uk, this is the song that got me addicted to the carpenters! 1 of their very best!*-1970: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=uaqoQr-aCtQ

        2. 'i just fall in love again' *not a single, considered too long for u.s. radio @ the time, but 'beautiful' doesn't even describe karen's vocals on this one :))))* 1977 https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=TXs6p1wAAlk

        3. 'they long to be close to you' *their first top 10 hit in the states, went to #1 on the hot 100 and became a huge top 10 hit worldwide incl. #6 in the uk, also 1 of richard's personal faves* 1970: https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=M268Csnue9I

        4. 'i won't last a day without you' *moderate hit, peaked @#11 over here & #32 in the uk, BUT karen's singing on this one is just pure ear candy!* 1974-https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=5VcbZ-fKsWE

        5. 'please mr. postman' *top 10 & top 5 worldwide smash, #1 over here and #2 in the uk. re-make of the 60s motown classic by the marvelettes. simple song, but karen could make any song sound great!* 1974 https://www.youtube.c*m/watch?v=jNn_UoI97GU
